{"id":"broadside-r9da.74","title":"relay.rs: add() does not check inbox_uri SSRF before DB insert","description":"LOCATION: src/relay.rs:65-92, relay::add()

FINDING: relay::add() performs an SSRF check on relay_url (the actor URL) and on inbox_uri extracted from the actor document. However, the SSRF check on inbox_uri at lines 70-79 resolves the host via is_private_host_resolved(). Between this check and the actual HTTP POST to inbox_uri (lines 127-134), there is a TOCTOU window where DNS rebinding can redirect the hostname to a private IP. This is the same DNS rebinding gap that the SsrfSafeResolver was designed to close on the main http_client — but relay.rs builds its own reqwest::Client at line 42 WITHOUT the SsrfSafeResolver. The client built in relay::add() has no custom DNS resolver, so DNS rebinding attacks on relay subscription are not prevented at the TCP connect level.

IMPACT: An attacker who controls DNS for a relay hostname can serve a valid actor document during the is_private_host_resolved check, then rebind DNS to 127.0.0.1 between the check and the TCP connection, causing an HTTP POST to an internal service.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"mark@reviewcommit.com","created_at":"2026-07-20T01:56:33.928421668Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-20T01:56:33.928421668Z","labels":["correctness","risk","review"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"broadside-r9da.74","depends_on_id":"broadside-r9da","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-07-20T01:56:33.964529856Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","metadata":"{}"}]}
